@article{ISI:000301897900012,
 abstract = {The structure of griseofulvic acid, C16H15ClO6, at 100 K has
orthorhombic (P2(1)2(1)2) symmetry. It is of interest with respect to
biological activity. The structure displays intermolecular O-H center
dot center dot center dot O, C-H center dot center dot center dot O
hydrogen bonding as well as week C-H center dot center dot center dot pi
and pi center dot center dot center dot pi interactions. In strong
acidic conditions the griseofulvin undergoes dimerization. The structure
of dimerized griseofulvin, C34H32C12O12 center dot C2H6O center dot H2O,
at 100 K has monoclinic (P2(1)) symmetry. The molecule crystallized as a
solvate with one ethanol and one water molecule. The dimeric molecules
form intermolecular O-H center dot center dot center dot O hydrogen
bonds to solvents molecules only but they interact via week C-H center
dot center dot center dot O, C-H center dot center dot center dot pi,
C-Cl center dot center dot center dot pi and pi center dot center dot
center dot pi interactions with other dimerized molecules.},
